reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fixed the ‘no heat’ issue!
reviews.reviewText: This simple part brought the heating element back to life in our GE dishwasher. After years of use the original part had become clogged resulting in the heating element being non-functioning. The installation of this new part (only takes 10-15 minutes to replace) was the cure all. Back in business - the dishes are clean and the drying cycle works! Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent replacement part for original GE float sensor (so far!)
reviews.reviewText: Day two of this piece being in our dishwasher (bought in 2016). I was worried we would have to scrap the dishwasher but learned this float sensor was a common issue with the dishes not going through the heated dry cycle. Watched a You Tube video on how to change this part out, found this one on Amazon and took a chance based on the reviews that this one would work instead of a genuine GE part, and voila! It worked. Saved me hundreds in a repairman cost — handy Mom to the rescue. Go me!
After reading online decided to try this part for a dishwasher that was not heating up. This fixed the issue and it is awesome to have dishes come out clean
Worked great on my GE Profile dishwasher. We thought we needed a new element until we did a little research. This fixed the issue. Was easy to replace and great price.
